# Zod `safeParse` in controllers

When validating request bodies with Zod, destructure the result so `success`, `error`, and `data` are explicit:

```typescript
const { success, error, data } = schema.safeParse(body);

if (!success) {
  return badRequest({ errors: error.flatten().fieldErrors });
}

const { ... } = data;
```

Do not assign the whole result to a single variable (e.g. `const parsed = schema.safeParse(body)`).
